## 5) OLED UI guide

### Main screen
Shows:
- Mode: `RX` or `TRAIN`
- Target tone (Hz)
- Estimated WPM
- SNR ratio (shown as `SNRx`)
- SNR bar
- Tail of RAW decoded text

### Menu access (PRG button)
- **Hold ~1s:** enter Menu / Select (depending on context)
- **Hold ~2s:** “Panic” back to main screen (from anywhere)

### Menu behaviour (deterministic)
Inside MENU:
- **Short press:** next menu item
- **Hold ~1s:** select menu item

### Menu items
- **Training:** Toggle training mode (can auto-calibrate)
- **Expand:** Toggle shorthand expansion into EXPANDED buffer
- **Calibrate:** Run tone detection and lock target frequency
- **Tone:** Adjust tone in 10 Hz steps
- **Sensitivity:** Adjust detector sensitivity
- **Squelch:** Adjust SNR gate threshold
- **LoRa Radio:** Toggle LoRa radio standby/sleep (if RadioLib)
- **Wi-Fi QR:** Show QR join screen for the AP (if QR supported)
- **Clear:** Clear RAW + EXPANDED buffers
- **Exit:** Return to main

### OLED power saving
- OLED sleeps after inactivity (default 5 minutes)
- Wakes on:
  - CW tone activity
  - button press

