## 11) Troubleshooting

### OLED is blank
Common causes:
- VEXT not enabled or wrong polarity
  - The sketch sets `VEXT_ON_LEVEL = LOW`
  - Some revisions need `HIGH`
- I2C pins differ on your board core definition

Try:
- Flip `VEXT_ON_LEVEL` from `LOW` to `HIGH`
- Confirm OLED pins match your board’s schematic

### Web UI doesn’t load
- Ensure you connected to the SoftAP SSID (not your normal Wi-Fi)
- Check IP via OLED QR screen or Serial output
- Default SoftAP IP is usually `192.168.4.1`

### Decoding is garbage / random characters
Almost always audio chain issues:
- ADC clipping (too much level)
- No mid-rail bias (audio swinging negative)
- Tons of noise or hum
- Wrong target tone (run calibrate)

Fixes:
- Reduce audio level
- Add proper bias/attenuation
- Calibrate again
- Increase squelch slightly

### It decodes but timing is weird
- Dot timing adapts based on your mark durations
- Very noisy conditions cause false short marks → dot estimate goes sideways

Fixes:
- Raise squelch slightly
- Reduce sensitivity slightly
- Improve audio filtering / tone purity

